commentary: Malinga to Musakanda, no run if that's straight onto boot, he's gone lbw, but umpire Gould disagrees. So Mathews opts fora review. Pretty awesome ball, to start things off. A yorker, that reverses into the right-hander, so very late. Said right-hander plays all around it, and might live to do the same again if he has got an inside edge on this. Oh, actually, the swing might well take it down leg. There appears to be no bat. The thing going for Malinga though is it hits the toe on the flush - so from there the ball-tracking will have to go on a straight line. Third umpire Nigel Llong has a decision to make. Hawk-Eye says it's only clipping leg stump, so the one-field umpire's call stands. Not out. And Sri Lanka lose their review

commentary: de Silva to Ervine, OUT goes for the sweep and misses...and the umpire's given it! It strikes him on leg stump and it's very full. Doesn't look out on first glance but it's been given. They have reviewed. This looks like it has marginally pitched in line. It's a slider from the bowler, so it's not spinning down a long way. In slow-mo, I reckon it will be umpire's call. In fact, it's hitting leg stump comfortably. It's not called umpire's call, technically, but the umpire's call was perfect. Good decision.

commentary: Williams to Mendis, 2 runs hangs back, without actually moving back, as he slices the ball from the stumps to the sweeper. Mendis hustles through for a second. Good work

commentary: Williams to Tharanga, SIX runs launches the short ball - there have been so so many from the Zimbabwe spinners - and Tharanga hammers it over deep midwicket quite handsomely. He's usually pristine on the off side, but here he's looking pretty good slogging too

commentary: Mumba to Mendis, no run offcutter on off stump, defends. And again, Mumba falls in his followthrough, tripping over his right leg. He keeps doing that because he runs in at an angle into the wickets, and then has to change direction immediately to avoid the danger area.

commentary: Mire to Tharanga, FOUR runs there it is. Only the second chase of 300 ever in Sri Lanka and both have come in this series. Tharanga wraps it up with a pull - indicative of the lengths Zimbabwe have insisted on bowling on this flat pitch, those tactics need to be looked at - and stays not out for the third innings in a row
